additional_house_rules:
Dear Guests,

Welcome to 161a - We are so glad to be hosting you in our home!

Originally built in 1890, the Devita Family purchased it in 1910 and three generations of Devitas went on to live here until 2015 when we became the grateful stewards of this home.  We wish that you take very good care of our home during your stay - thank you!

Some important details for your stay:

- Enjoy the guests basket of goodies and bottle of wine. Please refrain from consuming any other food or alcohol in the house- as this is our family home we often leave cabinets and fridge with food for our later consumption. 

-Feel free to use the kitchen cooking equipment, spices, and oils. Be sure to clean-up after cooking. A kitchen left excessively dirty from cooking will result in an additional $50 cleaning fee.

- Feel free to occupy the bottom shelf of the fridge and help yourself to any condiments inside.

- There is a cord and remote control to plug a device to for audio from the Bose speaker at the front of the house on the garden level. Please keep sound reasonable in our family friendly neighborhood.

- No parties. Please notify us if you are planning to have any visitors.

- When using the yard please be friendly and mindful of our neighbors, again as this is our family home and our relationships with our neighbors is very important. No outdoor use after 9:30 p.m.

- The couch folds open to a comfy bed. All of the bedding is in the cabinet to the left, directly across from the couch. 

- Notice the shades behind the lace curtains that you can draw down for privacy.

- Trash: The small silver container in the Kitchen is for compost, which can be taken out front and put in the brown NYC compost bin. All other recycling and trash are cans are marked accordingly. 

- There is a laundromat across the street on 23rd and 4th Ave. You can drop off/pick up if you choose.

Be gentle to our old home and have a cozy time during your stay in Brooklyn!

Your honored hosts,

Erica and Ken
description:
Hello and welcome to our original Brooklyn 1890's townhouse. Enjoy the original fireplace, wood floors, tin ceiling and garden! We are only 2 blocks from R train and you can reach Manhattan in 15 minutes. It is several stops away from the Atlantic Center and you can go anywhere. Our historic house is perfect for couples, families (with children), business travelers, small groups. I can not wait to host you!

The home was built in 1890 and the same family owned it for over 100 years. Much of the original details are preserved through gorgeous wood floors, marble fireplaces, tin ceilings, and a spectacular garden.

You have access to main apartment which is on the first two floors with fully private entry.

We are available by email, text, and phone and typically greet all of our guests.

South Slope / Greenwood Heights epitomizes Brooklyn through its incredible diversity of people and cultures, homes and industries, and captivating history. 
(URL HIDDEN)

R train to everywhere, especially via Atlantic Terminal just a few stops away!
